# Integration Test Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.test.local and fill in your test database credentials

# ============================================================================
# Test Supabase Configuration
# ============================================================================
# IMPORTANT: Use a separate test Supabase project or local instance
# DO NOT use production database for integration tests!

# Test Supabase Project URL
TEST_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-test-project.supabase.co

# Test Supabase Anon Key (public key)
TEST_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_test_anon_key_here

# Test Supabase Service Role Key (admin key - required for test setup/cleanup)
# ⚠️ This key bypasses RLS - only use in test environment!
TEST_SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=your_test_service_role_key_here

# ============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ============================================================================
#
# Option 1: Separate Test Supabase Project (Recommended)
# 1. Create new Supabase project at https://app.supabase.com
# 2. Name it "[ProjectName]-test"
# 3. Run same database migrations as main project
# 4. Get credentials from Settings > API
# 5. Fill in TEST_SUPABASE_* variables above
#
# Option 2: Local Supabase Instance
# 1. Install Supabase CLI: npm install -g supabase
# 2. Run: npx supabase start
# 3. Use local credentials (printed in terminal)
# 4. Fill in TEST_SUPABASE_* variables above
#
# Option 3: Same Project (Not Recommended)
# If you must use the same project:
# - Be very careful with data cleanup
# - Use unique test data markers
# - Consider using a separate schema
#
# ============================================================================
# Notes
# ============================================================================
#
# - Integration tests will create and delete real data
# - Tests clean up after themselves, but failures may leave orphaned data
# - All test users have emails ending in @test.com
# - Service role key is needed to bypass RLS for test setup
# - Do NOT commit .env.test.local to version control
#
